HEADWORD: Dixiecrats
<hw>Dixiecrats</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a former political party in the
US; formed in 1948 by Southern Democrats opposed to the candidacy of
<person>Harry S. Truman</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> States' Rights Democratic Party.</syn>⟦br⟧
